traits.description: There was once a pirate lord who invade every planet and every faction that he feels like to. No one dare to stand and against him, however, there were seven warrior who challenged him. After a whole night of battle, the pirate lord was defeated. his battle skill must be getting out of control to earn this title.
traits.name: piratelord

traits.description: Timmy is an Explorer. Their travels through the land have granted them insight into numerous schools of both magic and might -- they are capable of learning abilities from almost any mage or fighter scroll. However, they possess no innate abilities of their own.

data.mod: Kure's Rimworld of Magic Class Expansion Pack

traits.name: explorer

traits.description: Timmy is an Architect, a mage that applies their magic to structures, allowing them to raise or destroy buildings at a moment's whim. Architects rarely directly engage their foes, they prefer to shape the landscape itself to be inhospitable to their enemies. Most of their spells can be cast from anywhere on the map.

data.mod: Kure's Rimworld of Magic Class Expansion Pack

traits.name: architect

traits.description: Either the body or mind of Timmy is one of insight and experience. While some find them old fashioned, others will respect their guidance.

data.mod: Vanilla Ideology Expanded - Memes and Structures

traits.name: elder

races.description: A baseline human, mostly unmodified by gene engineering and mostly unchanged by evolutionary pressures on non-Earth planets.
races.name: human

races.description: Kijins are ogres who were evolved alikes of humans. Their huge bodies and muscles have shrunk, but the muscles are more dense and stronger. They still have to eat a lot to keep themselves up.
races.name: Kijin

races.description: A bloodthirsty vulpine near-human.
races.name: Revia

races.description: They are the parents of yokai that look just like people. They are special yokai that have sex and reproduce. They run the affairs of the Yokai Village in place of the fickle Tsuzurao, who usually wanders from place to place. Oni is the general leader of the group. It is said that he is a descendant of the 鬼, the root of all Yokai, but this is not certain. They may look like a slightly larger version of a human, but they are far superior to humans in terms of arm strength, leg strength, and endurance.
races.name: Oni

races.description: The term yokai half is used to refer to those who are a mixture of yokai and human blood. Their roots vary, but because one of their ancestors had a child with a yokai, their blood contains the power of the yokai. They have inherited the tradition of the Yokai Village, which respects close quarters combat, so they are strong in close quarters combat, but they are not good at using long range weapons. They also react strongly to psychic attacks and poisons, and have a weakness for tasting their food. In the Yokai Village, a human is considered a full-fledged adult at the age of 15, but a yokai half is considered a full-fledged adult at 18, and does not reach biological maturity until after the age of 30.
races.name: Yokai Half

races.description:
Arachne race lineage can be traced back to Arachne homeworld where the temperature fluctuate between cold and warm.
Arachnes over thousands of generations began to adapt to these temperature and ables themselves to withstand cold but in return have less tolerance to the heat
races.name: arachne

races.description:
A race of humanlike robots which are mostly female in model variety.

The origins of these machines are mostly unknown. Some speculate they are escapees from a civilization which used them for labor and some just suggest they are outdated pleasure machines which got dumped by a passing space freighter.

By design by their previous masters they are weak physically but their raw fortitude is enough to make up for it. Beware of their biological reactor and capacitors violently exploding, if they die by overheating.
races.name: Android

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike worker robots.

Usually found toiling around in colonies around the rim which got a resident tinkerer.

Not capable of sapience, however their relative cheap cost and ability to work around the clock make them valuable workers.
races.name: Droid

races.description:
A race of rudimentary humanlike warrior robots.

Usually found guarding the homes of the wealthy and offices of mega corporations. They show no mercy upon targets who fail to identify themselves. Are traditionally armed with miniguns and core launchers.
races.name: Battle droid

races.description:
This dryad caste bears a strong resemblance to humans, some individuals are even capable of verbal communication. However, in the vast majority of cases, they are not intelligent, and even rare manifestations of personality are an illusion created by their behavior pattern. Their caste is universal, thanks to which they can always significantly help the settlement.

In general, dryads are mammal-like creatures that have a symbiotic relationship with the Gauranlen tree. They reproduce together with their tree, which contains a hidden dryad queen. Dryads can morph into various specialized castes.
races.name: royaldryad

races.description:
Valkyries - an ancient race created to resist the mechanoids. Despite all the genetic changes, they are almost indistinguishable from humans in appearance, with the exception of the not rare presence of tails, horns, additional pairs of ears and other minor distinguishing features. How and by whom they were created has long been lost in time, but representatives of this race can still be found today in the expanses of the rimworld.<color=#a2c8ff>

According to the original idea, mutations were supposed to be a replacement for the degradation of organs and not be so obvious. However, with the change of generations, less "human" and more "alien" representatives of this race began to appear, some of which are only indirectly related to the Valkyries.

One of the significant genetic deviations was the complete degeneration of the male half of this race, which is why this race consists entirely of girls and was called the Valkyries. But despite this, the representatives of the Valkyries race have full compatibility with non-genetically modified humans, thanks to which they have not become extinct.</color>

With age, even the laziest Valkyrie has a very good "natural preparation" of the body, which is why these girls are always very dangerous in close combat.
races.name: valkyrie

races.description:
Equipment: Living Form - small humanoid helpers. They are miniature copies of the Valkyries, their bodies are subject to the same mutations and aberrations. They were created to simplify the life of the Valkyries, helping to treat wounds, cooking and psychological assistance. The fate of the ELFs was similar, after the closure of the project, they dispersed around the world.<color=#a2adff>

ELFs are considered adults from the age of 6, and their height does not exceed 1 meter. They are incapable of reproduction and new ELFs are reared in "mechanical eggs". To create them, the Valkyrie gene is used. Most organs are created with mechanites. Their bodies are small and light, and they can also hover in the air, but only for a short period of time.</color>

Despite the difficulties of creating ELFs, they meet no less than the Valkyries, however, they cannot answer who creates them and where they come from. According to one of the assumptions, the Mechanoids use them for their own purposes, and some unsuccessful or decommissioned copies fall into the wild.
races.name: elf

races.description:
A rare subspecies of Valkyrie that hybridizes with Gauranlen sprouts.

Usually mutations change Valkyries slightly, an additional tail, an eye, or unusual abilities. In the case of the Dryad Mother, the mutation brought about significant changes in both body structure and brain structure, creating separate subspecies.<color=#f5ffa2>

Dryad mothers do not experience emotions, and the reproductive system has been modified so that they are able to "give birth" to small mammalian creatures - dryads. Dryads "born" by the Mother are different from the usual, although they have a direct relationship. They are something like a biomass that has no mind and is controlled directly by the Mother. The process of birth itself has nothing to do with how it occurs in mammals, since the biomass simply falls away from the Mother like shed skin. The mucus of the bomass itself accumulates on the body of the Dryad along with sweat, or rather it is. The biomass covering the entire body of the Mother exists in synbiosis with her, protecting her from the effects of the external environment. The disadvantage is the flammability of biomass.</color>

Despite her size, the Dryad Mother is very heavy, which limits her mobility, however, despite the fact that she is slow, she can still deftly dodge blows.

Also on their heads, along with their hair, leaves grow like those of the Gauranlen tree, so leaves can fall from the Mother's head. Sometimes, instead of leaves of Gauranlen, a seed may fall from it.
races.name: dryadmother

races.description:
Herrschers is a mechanoid-enhanced version of the Valkyries, more precisely, it is an interpretation of the Valkyries by mechanoids. Like their not-so-distant cousins ​​ELFs, Herrschers were artificially created by machines. The versions of Herrscher you see today have little to do with those invincible hybrids of machine and organics, but they are able to think and make decisions for themselves. As with the Valkyries, knowledge of the Herrscher's past has been lost, and how they got free remains a mystery.

<color=#cca2ff>Herrschers are not too different from Valkyries. They are subject to the same diseases, mutations, abnormalities and are one of the closest sub-races to the original. The main difference is the skin of the Herrschers. If Valkyries skin becomes like stone. Herrscher's skin resembles plasteel, which affects not only survivability but also allows them to fight with crushing force with their bare hands.</color>
races.name: herrscher

races.description: Heyras settled in Rimworld a long time ago. They possess a unique psychic ability to, occasionally, hear whispers in their heads. Despite these whispers being mostly scattered words, Heyras believe they are the oracles of God. We do not know if these whispers are real. But it is confirmed that Heyras have a higher psychic sensitivity than humans.
races.name: Heyra

races.description: These savage barbarians are the nemesis of Heyras. They have thrown away the sense of moral and pursuit the primal pleasure. A series of evidence indicates that Rong is a separated branch of Heyra, although the Supreme Hierarch of Heyra denies this in all her strength.
races.name: Rong

races.description:
A humanoid race living in cities under the sea. Having traits similar to sea creatures, their blood contains substances that can be used for various medical uses.

Descendants of glitterworld explorers who settled in the deep sea, generations of body modifications has led to their current form. Spreading far and wide into the rim, they built many cities and prospered. Until now.
races.name: Moyo

races.description: A subspecies of the Moyo race, usually babies born after a Moyo is fertilized by a creature infected with the deep-sea virus. And because the symbiotic virus affects, most of them have strange personalities, but not intrinsically bad.
races.name: Red Moyo

races.description:
The Half-Dragons have been a space faring race for quite a long time, contrary to popular belief these noble yet somewhat savage folk are not genetically engineered. They are easily spotted by their physical differences with humans thanks to their colorful scales, draconic eyes, horns and even tails! Thanks to their physical differences and strong scales people of this race proved themselves to be excellent melee combatants. It was easy to find them serving various empires outside of their own as front line fighters.

      Sadly due to their hardy nature and exotic looks many Half-Dragons end up captured and forced into gladiatorial combat. There are other reasons they are highly sought after; unique biological traits that are wholly unique to them. One of which allows to combine a specialized ore with their blood that activates various powerful abilities.

      A point of debate of many scholars is how such a openly savage race had made it to spaceflight, much less a force that roams about the galaxy. This is in large part thanks to a rare sub group of Half-Dragons that lead their kind in political, cultural and scientific endeavors. These "albino's" are almost the polar opposites of their more common brutish brethren. Despite a strong imperial nation and a sense of loyalty to their own, those that find themselves able to escape their gladiatorial slavery often form up as pirates. These pirates tend to be ruthless and a general nuisance in the galaxy.
races.name: Half-Dragon

races.description: Epona is a humanoid creature whose origin is completely unknown except that it has its origin in Glitterworld. Some scholars view Epona as a kind of chimera with insects, not a gene-binding race with horses. Whatever the truth is. Epona considers themselves a centaur. They have established their own kingdoms in the name of horses in Rimworlds on the periphery.
races.name: Epona

races.description: This is Epona, which has become huge due to a problem with the gene called Destrier Syndrome. Only women get Destrier syndrome and get stronger to match their size, but they become a little stupid.
races.name: Destrier

races.description: Uniponen is a male epona with horns. The male incarnation of the goddess Epona. They are beautiful, but above all they have medicinal properties in their horns, so they are often hunted by foreign mercenaries and poachers in the Empire.
races.name: Uniponen

races.description: An all-female race of humans spliced with fox genes. Originally, they were Glitterworld designermates from the planet Aolara, but an internal war forced them to leave their homeworld. Now they are spread among the rim.
races.name: Kurin

races.description:
The Naga are a technologically advanced race without a functional goverment or law enforcement since their homeworld has become inhabitable.  This means they can be found mostly on space stations and ships and occassionally on Rimworlds as well.

They tend to work as mercenaries for the highest bidder and offer their superior skills with guns. Not just as excellent shooters, but also as weapon manufacturers. Their plasma technology is only rivaled by the charge weapons of glitterworlds. Naga are also known for their regenerative abilities and proficiency at disassembling mechanoids.

Despite this their way of life does not go well with others and thus they struggle to find allies among other races.

Good at: Shooting, Butchering, Mechanoid Disassembly, Psychics, Quality Crafting/Construction
Bad at: Melee, Plants, Animals, Enduring Pain
races.name: naga

races.description:
Draconic humanoids with extraordinary combat abilities - the solark. Ancient records state that the solark were made as the successors to the neclose and xenoorca, their sister races. Solark tend to live primitive, brutal lifestyles since their Creator's fall.

By some unthinkable means, the solark have an organ that acts as a small antimatter reactor. This organ, termed a furnace, allows its owner to create controlled antimatter explosions.

The draconic traits of the solark seem to derive from the genes of ancient Earth life. Solarkian scales provide strong natural armor, enough to stop many ordinary weapons outright. Solarkian strength is also remarkable, outperforming almost any other race with ease. On some worlds, solark are rumored to be strong enough to topple a building in one strike.

Unfortunately, solark must consume vast quantities of food to fuel their powerful bodies. Moreover, their killer claws lack dexterity, reducing their capacity for skilled labor. This combined with their unique morphology also means they can't use weapons or tools of any kind. Lastly, solark regulate their furnaces based on ambient air temperature. As a result, sudden changes in temperature can be hazardous to them. Exposure to open flames in particular is to be avoided at all costs.
races.name: Solark

races.description:
Amphibious, predatory humanoids with a lower body akin to a marine mammal's - the xenoorca. They are natural born warriors originally created as living bioweapons.

Xenoorca inherit the strong muscles and tough skin of certain Earth marine mammals. Their insulated bodies have a high metabolic rate, causing them to thrive in the cold but suffer in the heat. These factors combine to make the xenoorca a race of ravenous, active huntresses. Like their sister races, the xenoorca also suffer from weak immune systems.

Reflecting their intended purpose, xenoorca tend to be cunning, brutal individuals. Most enjoy the thrill of a hunt and offer their quarry no mercy. Still, some usual or adaptive individuals can learn to live in mixed-race societies. Such communities come to discover a cheerful yet mischievous side of xenoorcan nature.
races.name: Xenoorca

races.description:
Herrschers is a mechanoid-enhanced version of the Valkyries, more precisely, it is an interpretation of the Valkyries by mechanoids. Like their not-so-distant cousins ​​ELFs, Herrschers were artificially created by machines. The versions of Herrscher you see today have little to do with those invincible hybrids of machine and organics, but they are able to think and make decisions for themselves. As with the Valkyries, knowledge of the Herrscher's past has been lost, and how they got free remains a mystery.

<color=#cca2ff>Herrschers are not too different from Valkyries. They are subject to the same diseases, mutations, abnormalities and are one of the closest sub-races to the original. The main difference is the skin of the Herrschers. If Valkyries skin becomes like stone. Herrscher's skin resembles plasteel, which affects not only survivability but also allows them to fight with crushing force with their bare hands.</color>
races.name: <color=#cca2ff>Herrscher</color>

races.description:
A humanoid race, difficult to distinguish from ordinary human women on the surface. In reality, they are half-human, half-artificia that inherit strengths from both lineages. As a collective, many societies call them mixed-race nexaga, or simply nexaga.

Most children born to artificia-human pairings are of the mother's race. This appears to be by the design of the enigmatic artifician Creator. Yet, in rare cases where the father's genes are particularly dominant, nexaga are born. Records suggest that any child conceived by a nexaga will also be a nexaga, without exception. 

Nexaga have few of their artifician forbearers' most recognizable characteristics. No nexaga can undergo acclimation or summon allies in combat, for example. Still, their hybridization offers them some notable advantages. From their human blood they inherit versatility and immune strength. Conversely, their artifician blood confers specialized proficiencies without any associated weaknesses.
races.name: nexaga
